<dl id="n42025f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42025f">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42025f"> 25(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> open his mind</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">For, just as there have always been thieves, drunkards, and malefactors in the world, so there have always been men and women who, under the pretext of opening their minds to each other for mutual comfort and edification, were giving themselves to every kind of iniquity and lust. <small> Chiniquy, <a name="CPWC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CPWC"><cite title="source">The Priest The Woman and The Confessional</cite></a> (n.d.) 124-5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
